sn22.53:1.1:
1
At Sāvatthī. "Bhikkhus, one who is engaged is unliberated;
one who is disengaged is liberated. Consciousness, bhikkhus, while standing, might stand engaged with form; based upon form, established upon form, with a sprinkling of delight, it might come to growth, increase, and expansion. Or consciousness, while standing, might stand (engaged with feeling … engaged with perception …) engaged with volitional formations; based upon volitional formations, established upon volitional formations, with a sprinkling of delight, it might come to growth, increase, and expansion.
